import React, {useState} from 'react' import { useParams } from "react-router-dom" const UpdateRestaurant = (props) => { const [name, setName] = useState(""); const [location, setLocation] = useState(""); const [priceRange, setPriceRange] = useState("Price Range"); const {id} = useParams(); console.log(id) return (
setName(e.target.value)} id="name" className="form-control" type="text" />
setLocation(e.target.value)} id="location" className="form-control" type="text" />
setPriceRange(e.target.value)} id="price_range" className="form-control" type="number" />
) } export default UpdateRestaurant
